# 🧠 3️⃣ STREAM API (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥🔥🔥)

---

## ✅ Definition

Stream API is used to **process collections of data in functional style**

---

## 💻 Example

```java
import java.util.*;

public class StreamDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(1,2,3,4,5);

        list.stream()
            .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)
            .forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}
```

---

## 🧠 Flow

```text
Collection → Stream → Filter → Process → Output
```

---

## 🔹 Common Methods

* filter()
* map()
* forEach()
* collect()

---

## 💻 Example

```java
list.stream()
    .map(n -> n * 2)
    .forEach(System.out::println);
```

---

# 🔥 Interview Q&A

👉 Difference: Collection vs Stream
→ Collection stores data, Stream processes data

---

👉 What is lazy evaluation?
→ Executes only when needed

